This is a continuation of the story game started here:

[SG][RP][SA] The Open Story: Deadlaus

It's an alternate universe to the official Mush story. Some of the characters are similar, but their backgrounds are very different.

We started this thread because the other one was close to the 999-post limit and soon to be locked. 99 pages in 8 days - that's how active this story is. Several characters are still open to be claimed by new players. Don't miss out!

It's not really an RPG. We're not trying to make our characters "win" anything, we're just having fun writing a story. You can make your character(s) anything you want, as long as they're not TOO powerful. And they can't act on OOC information. We're ALL gods here, and we can rewrite history if something doesn't make sense.

Condensed Summary:

The story began in chaos. Some bombs went off, then aliens robbed a bank. Billionaire Harry Maubrick hired a crazy freighter pilot to drop some elephants into the city park, in a bizarre plot to take over the 5 largest corporations in Sol via mind-control devices. The pilot, Steve, kidnapped an elephant trainer named Jessica and forced her to unlock the zoo. After he completed the mission, he kept her in a cage in his basement.

Some mysterious strangers from a ship called Bertha began beaming to various places, causing havoc wherever they went. There was a rooftop battle between the aliens and the XCOM SWAT team. Steve dropped a cargo load of potato chips over the battle, but was caught by an SDF pilot named Charles Quartz, who forced him to land at a military base for interrogation. A rogue military called Exalt attacked the base looking for Jessica, and tracked her to Steve's house from the identification markings on his cargo plane.

John Fletcher, the "Shadow Boss" and CEO of Crossbow Technologies, decided to break away from Earth and form Crossbow Republics. He gathered up all the Elves and planned to embark on a voyage to find a new planet to colonize. The Council of 5 (now 4) decided to set up protection zones to defend the Earth from the alien attack.

After Maubrick's plot failed, he realized that the mind-control devices he purchased from Crossbow were all defective, and suspected sabotage. He began buying up Crossbow stock, attempting a hostile take-over, but he was arrested for insider trading. All the stock was sold off, and the market crashed. A wealthy coffee-drinker named Stark bought up 99% percent of the company.

The Exalt forces at the military base were defeated and captured. Steve discovered that he could walk through walls, and made a desperate attempt to escape the base in a jet. Along the way, he saved a man's life, but got seriously injured just as he reached the jet. Charles took him to the hospital, then offered him a job as a fighter pilot - his dream come true.

The Shadow Boss sent in an aerial team to retrieve some people in cryo storage at the base, but failed. Air support came to defend the base, and Charles' team defeated the Crossbow jets in an intense dogfight. The Shadow Boss fired a laser from orbit, destroying the base. The Crossbow republic launched their voyage to the new planet.

Jessica turned out to be a doctorate biologist, whose thesis would be somehow instrumental. She evaded Exalt's attempt to capture her, and the US Military rescued her and her cat, Darwin. They were going to take her to meet with the Secretary of Science and Technology, but an alien attack killed her military escort. NADO forces evacuated her to a different military base, where she met Dr. Colin Pierce, a strange punk scientist who was interested in her work.

Charles and Steve came to the same base where Jessica was. Steve failed miserably in the flight simulator and then Jessica attacked him when they met in the hallway. Bertha's technician and psychologist, Terry and Dawn, beamed right into the fight, and Jessica ran off. The Bertha had been destroyed, and most of its crew were dead, except for those two, and the "Pathfinder", Samuel.

The Mush Queen was a slave to the aliens who were invading Earth. She killed the aliens' Uber-Ethereal and took his power, and then killed most of the other Ethereals and took their power. She is currently sleeping to transform herself to hold all that power, but if she awakes, the Earth is doomed.

Under the Mush Queen's powers, some humans transformed into monsters and attacked the people at the base. A badass chef named Chef sizzled them to a crisp with his flame-thrower. Stark ordered analysis of the monsters.

(Let me know if I missed anything or got anything wrong.)
